1
00:01:01,357 --> 00:01:05,566
When people finish their day
and hurry home,

2
00:01:06,187 --> 00:01:08,104
my day starts.

3
00:01:25,437 --> 00:01:29,187
My diner is open from midnight
to 7:00 in the morning.

4
00:01:30,181 --> 00:01:33,556
They call it "Midnight Diner."

5
00:01:36,013 --> 00:01:37,673
PORK MISO COMBO, BEER, SAKE, SHOCHU

6
00:01:37,673 --> 00:01:39,680
That's all I have on my menu.
PORK MISO COMBO, BEER, SAKE, SHOCHU

7
00:01:39,787 --> 00:01:45,527
But I make whatever customers request,
as long as I have ingredients for it.

8
00:01:45,527 --> 00:01:47,754
That's my policy.

9
00:01:51,802 --> 00:01:53,795
Do I even have customers?

10
00:01:53,795 --> 00:01:55,815
More than you would expect.

11
00:01:58,156 --> 00:02:01,336
MIDNIGHT DINER: TOKYO STORIES

12
00:02:01,336 --> 00:02:05,711
SALMON AND MUSHROOMS

13
00:02:07,666 --> 00:02:09,125
Here you go.

14
00:02:10,450 --> 00:02:11,616
Here you are.

15
00:02:13,316 --> 00:02:15,566
Here you are.

16
00:02:21,708 --> 00:02:23,125
Everyone's so quiet.

17
00:02:23,754 --> 00:02:26,212
Autumn is the best time for good food.

18
00:03:03,006 --> 00:03:03,868
Here you go.

19
00:03:04,213 --> 00:03:07,768
Grilled salted salmon
and mushrooms sauteed in butter.

20
00:03:07,768 --> 00:03:09,302
I've been waiting for it.

21
00:03:11,515 --> 00:03:12,741
This fragrance...

22
00:03:13,173 --> 00:03:14,631
-Thank you.
-Thank you.

23
00:03:15,148 --> 00:03:17,661
Master, another whiskey sour, please.

24
00:03:17,661 --> 00:03:18,514
Sure.

25
00:03:18,514 --> 00:03:20,898
Mr. Uehara and Kimie are a married couple

26
00:03:20,898 --> 00:03:24,764
who runs a barbershop
called Barber Uehara.

27
00:03:25,209 --> 00:03:27,341
Sometimes they come here together.

28
00:03:27,341 --> 00:03:29,036
The mushrooms are delicious.

29
00:03:30,018 --> 00:03:31,446
The salmon is delicious, too.

30
00:03:32,866 --> 00:03:34,962
Where are you two from?

31
00:03:35,322 --> 00:03:37,291
I'm from Nemuro in Hokkaido.

32
00:03:37,539 --> 00:03:38,708
I'm from Nagano.

33
00:03:38,986 --> 00:03:40,486
Deep in the mountains of Kiso.

34
00:03:41,680 --> 00:03:43,328
That explains your tastes.

35
00:03:43,936 --> 00:03:47,327
My dad would often send me out
to hunt for mushrooms in the fall.

36
00:03:47,587 --> 00:03:49,831
As a kid, a fisherman my family knew

37
00:03:49,831 --> 00:03:51,956
used to give us fresh salmon every year.

38
00:03:52,893 --> 00:03:54,310
By the way, Kimie,

39
00:03:54,616 --> 00:03:57,530
you said you might travel to Shanghai
with your friend.

40
00:03:57,798 --> 00:03:58,793
Are you going?

41
00:03:59,040 --> 00:04:00,913
Yes, I decided to go.

42
00:04:01,868 --> 00:04:02,626
When?

43
00:04:02,955 --> 00:04:03,888
Day after tomorrow.

44
00:04:03,888 --> 00:04:06,658
It's a five-night all-you-can-eat tour
to eat crabs.

45
00:04:07,600 --> 00:04:10,140
I'm so jealous! I love Shanghai crabs.

46
00:04:10,517 --> 00:04:12,056
This is the best season for them.

47
00:04:12,423 --> 00:04:13,381
Here you are.

48
00:04:13,991 --> 00:04:15,641
Are you staying home,
Mr. Uehara?

49
00:04:15,965 --> 00:04:16,794
Yes.

50
00:04:17,342 --> 00:04:19,799
Kimie has always wanted to go to Shanghai,

51
00:04:20,106 --> 00:04:22,769
but we had to prioritize the business.

52
00:04:23,229 --> 00:04:24,818
-It'll be a nice break.
-Yeah.

53
00:04:25,825 --> 00:04:26,908
Well,

54
00:04:27,573 --> 00:04:29,309
what a thoughtful husband!

55
00:04:30,905 --> 00:04:32,863
It's only one week, so I'll be fine...

56
00:04:33,575 --> 00:04:34,741
on my own.

57
00:04:37,950 --> 00:04:40,110
That's what Mr. Uehara said,

58
00:04:40,658 --> 00:04:43,322
but the day after Kimie left for Shanghai,

59
00:04:43,646 --> 00:04:47,572
he started coming to my place
almost every night.

60
00:05:01,438 --> 00:05:03,723
I'm fine when I'm in the shop,

61
00:05:04,200 --> 00:05:05,909
but when I'm home alone,

62
00:05:06,221 --> 00:05:09,003
I get restless and anxious.

63
00:05:09,320 --> 00:05:12,195
It makes me want to go
somewhere with people.

64
00:05:14,410 --> 00:05:15,956
Another beer, please.

65
00:05:16,379 --> 00:05:16,938
Sure.

66
00:05:17,664 --> 00:05:20,693
Kimie is out spreading
her wings in Shanghai,

67
00:05:21,035 --> 00:05:24,957
so I think it's okay
if you do some unwinding, too. Right?

68
00:05:25,240 --> 00:05:26,778
Don't worry about it.

69
00:05:27,278 --> 00:05:28,155
Actually,

70
00:05:28,635 --> 00:05:30,831
I just went to pachinko for
the first time in a long time.

71
00:05:30,831 --> 00:05:32,796
I lost 30,000 yen.

72
00:05:33,525 --> 00:05:35,287
You've unwound too much.

73
00:05:35,704 --> 00:05:37,954
I got a little too deep.

74
00:05:42,651 --> 00:05:43,610
Thank you.

75
00:05:48,675 --> 00:05:51,955
Is Mr. Uehara going to be okay like that?

76
00:05:52,210 --> 00:05:56,231
Don't worry about it.
Kimie will be back in a few days.

77
00:05:59,534 --> 00:06:00,236
Welcome.

78
00:06:00,764 --> 00:06:02,358
Good evening.

79
00:06:07,463 --> 00:06:08,500
Good evening.

80
00:06:11,115 --> 00:06:12,199
Welcome.

81
00:06:14,218 --> 00:06:17,968
So you two are childhood friends?

82
00:06:18,517 --> 00:06:20,650
We used to be neighbors.

83
00:06:20,992 --> 00:06:24,902
When I was looking for someone to
teach my new staff how to put on kimonos,

84
00:06:24,902 --> 00:06:26,181
we crossed paths again.

85
00:06:27,061 --> 00:06:30,394
It was such a surprise.
It's been decades since we last met.

86
00:06:31,643 --> 00:06:32,896
You teach how to put on kimonos?

87
00:06:32,896 --> 00:06:33,608
Yes.

88
00:06:34,584 --> 00:06:37,584
I lived in Kansai for a long time
after I had got married,

89
00:06:38,365 --> 00:06:41,906
but my husband passed away last year,
and I came here.

90
00:06:43,981 --> 00:06:44,898
Here you go.

91
00:06:51,951 --> 00:06:53,118
You're very good.

92
00:06:55,223 --> 00:06:57,390
Master, some pickles, please.

93
00:06:58,697 --> 00:06:59,530
Sure.

94
00:07:02,263 --> 00:07:03,721
My name is Sayoko Kagami.

95
00:07:04,188 --> 00:07:06,146
It's nice to meet you.

96
00:07:14,355 --> 00:07:16,396
Maybe it's just me, but...

97
00:07:17,115 --> 00:07:19,678
you look like you've regained your youth.

98
00:07:21,300 --> 00:07:23,133
That's amazing!

99
00:07:23,728 --> 00:07:24,895
Can you tell?

100
00:07:26,869 --> 00:07:29,203
Could it be love?

101
00:07:30,088 --> 00:07:31,422
No!

102
00:07:31,999 --> 00:07:33,342
I've been getting shaves.

103
00:07:33,735 --> 00:07:34,694
Shaves?

104
00:07:35,616 --> 00:07:38,355
You know Mr. Uehara who was just here?

105
00:07:38,770 --> 00:07:39,884
He's a barber.

106
00:07:40,228 --> 00:07:43,010
He's actually really good at it.

107
00:07:43,179 --> 00:07:45,928
When he touches your face,

108
00:07:46,426 --> 00:07:50,304
you can tell he has softer hands
than other men.

109
00:07:50,304 --> 00:07:53,756
Especially the balls of his fingertips...

110
00:08:00,181 --> 00:08:01,357
Welcome.

111
00:08:02,062 --> 00:08:03,445
Are you closed already?

112
00:08:04,150 --> 00:08:05,108
No.

113
00:08:06,298 --> 00:08:07,798
I don't have a reservation.

114
00:08:09,059 --> 00:08:12,079
Could I just ask for a shave?

115
00:08:13,835 --> 00:08:14,752
Of course.

116
00:08:54,581 --> 00:08:55,457
I'm sorry.

117
00:08:56,708 --> 00:08:58,417
My earlobes are sensitive.

118
00:09:00,704 --> 00:09:01,777
Should I stop?

119
00:09:02,000 --> 00:09:03,041
No.

120
00:09:03,585 --> 00:09:04,789
Keep going.

121
00:09:05,559 --> 00:09:06,392
Yes.

122
00:09:24,726 --> 00:09:25,767
Here's your change.

123
00:09:28,100 --> 00:09:29,400
I'm sorry.

124
00:09:29,779 --> 00:09:31,449
I've made you close late.

125
00:09:31,736 --> 00:09:33,236
No, don't worry about it.

126
00:09:33,897 --> 00:09:36,189
I heard about you at a restaurant.

127
00:09:36,788 --> 00:09:37,975
Is that so?

128
00:09:38,682 --> 00:09:39,859
It was better than expected.

129
00:09:40,152 --> 00:09:42,099
Thank you very much.

130
00:09:43,162 --> 00:09:47,456
Can you join me for dinner?
If you don't mind.

131
00:09:48,048 --> 00:09:50,965
It's on me.
As thanks for staying open late.

132
00:09:52,239 --> 00:09:54,448
No, it was nothing...

133
00:09:55,334 --> 00:09:56,167
Actually...

134
00:09:57,253 --> 00:09:58,628
I'm on my own tonight.

135
00:10:00,364 --> 00:10:01,364
Please?

136
00:10:04,806 --> 00:10:07,104
DINER

137
00:10:07,104 --> 00:10:09,467
Were the Shanghai crabs good?
DINER

138
00:10:09,908 --> 00:10:12,725
Yes, I ate as much as I possibly could.

139
00:10:13,406 --> 00:10:15,365
This mooncake is really good.

140
00:10:17,105 --> 00:10:19,852
In Japan we eat dango
while gazing at the moon,

141
00:10:20,216 --> 00:10:23,216
but in China they eat these mooncakes.

142
00:10:26,117 --> 00:10:29,701
Mr. Uehara was acting
a little strange while you were gone.

143
00:10:30,000 --> 00:10:31,417
Really?

144
00:10:32,341 --> 00:10:36,018
He's no good without his wife around.

145
00:10:36,018 --> 00:10:37,025
Here you go.

146
00:10:37,556 --> 00:10:40,685
Shanghai crabs are good,
but salmons are still my favorite.

147
00:10:40,937 --> 00:10:43,765
This salmon is caught from wild
in the Sea of Okhotsk.

148
00:10:44,072 --> 00:10:45,192
I'm so excited!

149
00:10:46,111 --> 00:10:48,655
By the way, the woman who came here...

150
00:10:49,343 --> 00:10:50,385
What's her name?

151
00:10:51,177 --> 00:10:53,031
The childhood friend of the hostess.

152
00:10:53,975 --> 00:10:55,910
Mrs. Sayoko, who teaches
how to put on kimonos.

153
00:10:56,068 --> 00:10:56,710
Her.

154
00:10:57,346 --> 00:10:58,555
Did she go to your shop?

155
00:11:00,266 --> 00:11:00,970
No.

156
00:11:01,933 --> 00:11:04,683
She was a real mature beauty, wasn't she?

157
00:11:04,683 --> 00:11:06,491
That kimono sure suited her.

158
00:11:07,213 --> 00:11:09,722
Master, can I have some rice, too?

159
00:11:10,078 --> 00:11:10,860
Sure thing.

160
00:11:11,546 --> 00:11:14,704
I'm glad to hear
you were able to relax, anyway.

161
00:11:15,156 --> 00:11:16,031
Indeed.

162
00:11:18,776 --> 00:11:21,554
I'm sorry for leaving everything to you
at the shop.

163
00:11:21,983 --> 00:11:23,691
It was nothing.

164
00:11:27,267 --> 00:11:29,022
Must be nice...

165
00:11:43,716 --> 00:11:44,925
One moment please.

166
00:11:49,211 --> 00:11:50,836
Hello, Barber Uehara.

167
00:11:52,282 --> 00:11:54,282
I see. Just a shave?

168
00:11:55,899 --> 00:11:57,066
At 3:00 tomorrow.

169
00:11:58,211 --> 00:11:59,377
And your name?

170
00:12:00,767 --> 00:12:02,850
Mrs. Sayoko Kagami.

171
00:12:07,107 --> 00:12:08,232
My apologies.

172
00:12:10,622 --> 00:12:13,872
We're looking forward to seeing you.
Thank you.

173
00:12:20,679 --> 00:12:22,138
Thank you very much.

174
00:12:32,627 --> 00:12:33,877
Are you okay?

175
00:12:34,890 --> 00:12:36,349
I saw you dropped your razor.

176
00:12:39,209 --> 00:12:40,459
I must be tired.

177
00:12:43,221 --> 00:12:46,888
Did something happen while I was gone?

178
00:12:48,992 --> 00:12:50,117
What do you mean?

179
00:12:56,470 --> 00:13:00,262
I won't get mad,
so please just don't lie to me.

180
00:13:17,091 --> 00:13:18,175
I'm sorry!

181
00:13:19,341 --> 00:13:20,258
Kimie...

182
00:13:20,972 --> 00:13:21,889
I...

183
00:13:26,341 --> 00:13:27,466
I'm sorry.

184
00:13:28,316 --> 00:13:30,483
This is the first time I've...

185
00:13:32,416 --> 00:13:33,874
It's your fault.

186
00:13:36,675 --> 00:13:39,540
Touching my face like that...

187
00:13:39,951 --> 00:13:42,367
I completely lost my senses.

188
00:13:44,466 --> 00:13:47,300
There are some things we have to do...

189
00:13:48,300 --> 00:13:51,383
even if we know they're wrong.

190
00:13:53,341 --> 00:13:54,383
Yes...

191
00:13:56,258 --> 00:13:57,258
I'll go...

192
00:13:58,132 --> 00:13:59,420
take a shower first.

193
00:13:59,987 --> 00:14:00,558
Yes.

194
00:14:10,664 --> 00:14:11,664
Can you...

195
00:14:15,576 --> 00:14:17,350
put on kimonos?

196
00:14:19,591 --> 00:14:20,674
No...

197
00:14:22,889 --> 00:14:25,680
Men used to know how to do it.

198
00:14:26,876 --> 00:14:31,210
They always made sure
a naked woman went home as a lady.

199
00:14:40,762 --> 00:14:43,595
So, he's completely terrified.

200
00:14:44,151 --> 00:14:47,401
His hands shake so much
he can't even hold a razor.

201
00:14:48,181 --> 00:14:51,113
What a fool. It's so pitiful.

202
00:14:52,522 --> 00:14:54,605
A former gangster's wife...

203
00:14:59,241 --> 00:15:02,491
She must have kept the room dark.

204
00:15:04,074 --> 00:15:07,991
But you'd think he would
still see her back, though...

205
00:15:08,941 --> 00:15:12,983
No, normally, you'd definitely see it...

206
00:15:20,864 --> 00:15:23,008
What's he doing now?

207
00:15:23,843 --> 00:15:24,968
He left.

208
00:15:25,593 --> 00:15:28,385
He's probably staying
in a capsule hotel or something.

209
00:15:35,383 --> 00:15:36,411
Master, beer, please.

210
00:15:36,871 --> 00:15:37,744
Sure.

211
00:15:41,761 --> 00:15:44,511
Everything had been
going almost too smoothly.

212
00:15:45,732 --> 00:15:48,773
We don't have kids,
so it's just the two of us

213
00:15:49,181 --> 00:15:51,848
doing the same thing everyday,
over and over again.

214
00:15:53,219 --> 00:15:54,224
Tell me, master.

215
00:15:54,529 --> 00:15:55,137
What?

216
00:15:55,866 --> 00:15:58,491
What sort of woman is Sayoko?

217
00:15:59,222 --> 00:16:00,695
You met her, right?

218
00:16:01,915 --> 00:16:02,749
Yeah.

219
00:16:04,770 --> 00:16:08,626
Is she so beautiful that men
just can't help but want her?

220
00:16:10,841 --> 00:16:12,365
I'm not sure.

221
00:16:15,680 --> 00:16:16,972
She's coming tomorrow.

222
00:16:17,671 --> 00:16:18,648
To the shop.

223
00:16:19,520 --> 00:16:20,228
What?

224
00:16:23,133 --> 00:16:24,842
I wonder how I'll feel.

225
00:16:44,922 --> 00:16:45,937
Welcome.

226
00:16:46,764 --> 00:16:49,285
I called in a reservation yesterday.

227
00:16:50,416 --> 00:16:51,649
I'm sorry,

228
00:16:52,106 --> 00:16:54,605
my husband is out on some urgent business.

229
00:16:57,031 --> 00:16:57,947
I see.

230
00:16:59,935 --> 00:17:00,769
Then...

231
00:17:01,469 --> 00:17:02,995
could you do it for me instead?

232
00:17:04,438 --> 00:17:05,945
Me? Are you sure?

233
00:17:07,081 --> 00:17:07,881
Please.

234
00:17:08,597 --> 00:17:09,617
You can, right?

235
00:17:13,004 --> 00:17:13,837
Yes.

236
00:18:16,176 --> 00:18:17,718
You're also very good.

237
00:18:18,537 --> 00:18:20,048
Thank you.

238
00:18:20,048 --> 00:18:22,200
I'll come again.

239
00:18:23,891 --> 00:18:24,933
Ten years...

240
00:18:26,073 --> 00:18:28,323
this shop has been open.

241
00:18:29,683 --> 00:18:30,933
It was our dream...

242
00:18:31,544 --> 00:18:34,877
to have our own shop even if it's small.

243
00:18:35,915 --> 00:18:36,933
Is that so?

244
00:18:37,491 --> 00:18:38,558
Therefore...

245
00:18:41,624 --> 00:18:43,249
please don't come again.

246
00:18:45,287 --> 00:18:46,245
Please.

247
00:18:47,696 --> 00:18:49,592
My husband apologizes as well.

248
00:19:00,611 --> 00:19:01,611
All right.

249
00:19:02,507 --> 00:19:04,090
Give my regards to him.

250
00:19:24,153 --> 00:19:25,028
Here you are.

251
00:19:29,502 --> 00:19:30,544
That woman...

252
00:19:31,849 --> 00:19:35,015
she knew that I knew.

253
00:19:37,411 --> 00:19:40,036
But she fell asleep in the chair.

254
00:19:42,812 --> 00:19:46,146
I was afraid my hands
would move on their own.

255
00:19:47,679 --> 00:19:51,387
I'm glad you were able to talk things out.

256
00:19:54,372 --> 00:19:55,497
Welcome.

257
00:20:04,082 --> 00:20:07,166
I got on a train to go back to Nagano...

258
00:20:09,120 --> 00:20:11,078
but I turned back halfway.

259
00:20:15,187 --> 00:20:16,354
How selfish of you.

260
00:20:18,437 --> 00:20:19,247
Sorry.

261
00:20:25,595 --> 00:20:27,637
Try it if you like.

262
00:20:41,651 --> 00:20:45,151
Salmon and mushrooms
are good on their own, but...

263
00:20:46,092 --> 00:20:47,175
I think...

264
00:20:48,362 --> 00:20:50,737
they're best together.

265
00:21:02,300 --> 00:21:03,012
Come on.

266
00:21:07,441 --> 00:21:09,066
Let's eat before they get cold.

267
00:21:19,373 --> 00:21:20,582
No cheating next time.

268
00:21:29,061 --> 00:21:30,049
Let's eat.

269
00:21:57,827 --> 00:22:01,427
Cut a large piece of tinfoil,
and wrap up the ingredients tightly.

270
00:22:01,427 --> 00:22:03,702
The aroma of the butter
will permeate the dish...

271
00:22:04,173 --> 00:22:06,798
without losing the salmon
and mushrooms' flavors.

272
00:22:16,981 --> 00:22:18,250
Master...

273
00:22:18,587 --> 00:22:22,170
You wouldn't happen to know
a good barbershop, would you?

274
00:22:22,992 --> 00:22:26,826
Don't tell her because the last place
prevented her from coming again.

275
00:22:27,599 --> 00:22:29,807
I thought he might be good in bed, too.

276
